6 AS INTRODUCED
7 An Act relating to electric vehicles; prohibiting
certain actions by electric vehicle charging
8 providers; requiring certain options for payment;
making certain exceptions; providing for
9 codification; and providing an effective date.
10
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
14 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 160.39 of Title 17, unless there
15 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
16 A. Electric vehicle charging providers that provide electric
17 vehicle charging stations that are open to the general public shall
18 not require a user to hold or obtain a membership, subscription, or
19 similar account to access or use the charging services. In
20 addition, providers shall not collect, store, or require any
21 personally identifiable information from users except for
22 information strictly necessary to complete the payment transaction.
23 Providers shall provide an option for users to pay through
24 universally accepted payment methods, including, but not limited to,
Req. No. 11636 Page 1

1 cred it cards, debit cards, or mobile payment systems, without
2 requiring any additional registration or disclosure of personal
3 data.
4 B. This section shall not apply to private charging stations or
5 those designated for exclusive use by specific individuals,
6 businesses, or organizations.
7 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
